<br>
Then, I tried quading the shadow thingies outside the TOFS. There are plenty of em to pull, but make sure to be fairly close when they get low on health so they don't scatter on you.  They also hit pretty hard and fast.  These are ok xp, but I can only stand to look at all the white on my screen for only so long from fighting in Velious.<br>
<br>
Throughout it all, the most consistent place was OT.  Get KEI, sow potions, and a focus item and you can single kite nearly non-stop if you stick with the berzerkers/thorny/stoneleer/Tigresses.  Yes, you can take the knights, stonegazers, tigers, and spiked, but they don't seem to give any more xp than the others even though they require a few more blasts to kill (meaning more mana spent for the same xp).  I never really liked quading here for some reason.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps a bit...<br>
<br>
Tsu<br>
