<br>
See the Comprehensive Quadding locations post below for instructions.  You will be heading to EW, Iceclad, DSP, or OT most likely.<br>
<br>
If quadding is not your thing, you might try soloing single pulls in those zones.  Velious is nice because you can work on you dwarf/veeshan faction for questing later.  In a couple of levels you might try Happ Drimblenod in Lesser Faydark.  She is a static spawn who gives no faction hits.  As a gnome it pains me to point you towards a fellow gnome for cheap experience but there it is.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bobbybrantly>bobbybrantly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/22/03 3:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=762.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> dwarves</span><hr size=1> To the people who have quaded stuff in EW, about how many %xp per quad do you get? I get 5% xp for every tri-kite of dwarves. I'm happy with that amount, but if EW is better, I think I will try it out tonight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=waxor>Waxor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/22/03 3:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=762.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://linux.wku.edu/~sporadic/gfx/llama.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing at LVL 37-39</span><hr size=1> oh.. one more thing.. just thoughts from my experiences in the following zones and what led me to EW:<br>
<br>
DSP: solo'd my shammy their alot.. root rot stuff.  but way too laggy on my machine to quad.  and lightcrawlers seem to outrun my jbooties (same in that seru place)<br>
<br>
OT: great single kites. did 30 something to 34 here single kiting and learned how to get around well in 3rd person. tried quads and had horrible pathing problems getting mobs to wrap and stack, adds warping on me, etc...<br>
<br>
IC: just never really tried it<br>
<br>
EW: just seem to fit. had my first success quading there. stayed there from 34-40.  was getting 5-7% per quad  in most of the levels.  xp dropped to around 4, sometimes 5% at 40.<br>
<br>
Now at 40, i've taken a liking to hanging out at the specs in the oasis. i'll lev, round em all up (7 or 8)  and kite em full speed til they drop to 4. then i'll BoF and finish quadin.<br>
<br>
good luck to ya<br>
-Waxar<br>
